to the editor peter w galbraith details the turkish kurdish problems that could be unleashed by war in iraq flashback for the kurds op ed feb 19 there is yet another angle to this story turkish policies of repression against the kurds were one of the strongest and most lasting arguments against admitting turkey to membership in the european union turkey 's application to the european union is still pending and is soon to be reviewed again support for a united states invasion of iraq may bring the turks billions in aid but it may also give them the much costlier choice between losing any chance for membership in the european union and tolerating a secessionist movement in the turkish parts of kurdistan which could endanger the very existence of turkey in its present form eckhard kuhn osius new york feb 19 2003

